benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: POST /1.0/kb/bundles/{bundleId}/block - Block a bundle

covered: POST valid payload creates BlockingState and returns HTTP 201 with a JSON array of BlockingState objects
POST with all optional parameters exercised (headers and query params) to validate full parameter support
Blocking with optional headers and body validation across scenarios (TC01–TC04) showing flexible input handling
Validation coverage including invalid bundleId format (400), non-existent bundle (404), missing header (400/401), missing body (400), malformed body (400), invalid date format (400)
Error handling coverage for service unavailability (503) and dependent service error (502/503)
Edge cases coverage for maximum/minimum BlockingState values (TC13, TC14), partial input (TC15), and injection/XSS (TC19, TC20)
Security coverage for authentication token issues (TC18) and mixed header scenarios
Error coverage for no data / not found scenarios (TC05, TC07)
Handling of extra parameters (TC12) with 201 and proper response
Performance testing under normal and peak loads (TC25, TC26), plus bulk/block scenarios (TC27)
Integration coverage for data consistency across systems (TC29) and dependent service errors (TC28)
Regression tests for special characters in BlockingState (TC23) and backward compatibility (TC24)
gaps: Duplicate submission handling is not explicitly tested (no test for idempotent/duplicate POST behavior)
Rate limiting / throttling scenarios are not covered
Caching behavior and headers (e.g., ETag, Cache-Control) are not tested
Explicit 403 Forbidden scenarios or broader authorization role testing are not clearly covered (beyond 401 in TC18)
500 Internal Server Error scenarios are not explicitly tested (only 503 / 502 in integration cases)
Duplicate or cross-test coverage for 201 responses with content-type verification is not explicit
recommendations: Add a test for duplicate submissions to ensure idempotency or graceful handling of duplicates
Introduce rate limiting/throttling tests to ensure proper handling under high request volume
Add tests validating caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) on POST responses when applicable
Add explicit 403Forbidden authorization tests to complement existing 401/400 coverage
Add a dedicated 500 Internal Server Error scenario (e.g., database failure) to validate server-side error handling
Consider a test validating response Content-Type and schema for 201 responses to ensure consistency across clients
